{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:lamentations.3",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "lamentations",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Lamentations 3 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:1",
      "text": "ALEPH. How will the gold be tarnished, and the fine silver changed! the sacred stones have been poured forth at the top of all the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:2",
      "text": "BETH. The precious sons of Zion, who were equalled in value with gold, how are they counted as earthen vessels, the works of the hands of the potter!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:3",
      "text": "GIMEL. Nay, serpents have drawn out the breasts, they give suck to their young, the daughters of my people are incurably cruel, as an ostrich in a desert.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:4",
      "text": "DALETH. The tongue of the sucking child cleaves to the roof of its mouth for thirst: the little children ask for bread, and there is none to break it to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:5",
      "text": "HE. They that feed on dainties are desolate in the streets: they that used to be nursed in scarlet have clothed themselves with dung.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:6",
      "text": "VAU. And the iniquity of the daughter of my people has been increased beyond the iniquities of Sodoma, the city that was overthrown very suddenly, and none laboured against her with their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:7",
      "text": "ZAIN. Her Nazarites were made purer than snow, they were whiter than milk, they were purified as with fire, their polishing was superior to sapphire stone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:8",
      "text": "HETH. Their countenance is become blacker than smoke; they are not known in the streets: their skin has cleaved to their bones; they are withered, they are become as a stick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:9",
      "text": "TETH. The slain with the sword were better than they that were slain with hunger: they have departed, pierced through from want of the fruits of the field.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:10",
      "text": "JOD. The hands of tender-hearted women have sodden their own children: they became meat for them in the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:11",
      "text": "CHAPH. The Lord has accomplished his wrath; he has poured out his fierce anger, and has kindled a fire in Sion, and it has devoured her foundations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:12",
      "text": "LAMED. The kings of the earth, even all that dwell in the world, believed not that an enemy and oppressor would enter through the gates of Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:13",
      "text": "MEM. For the sins of her prophets, and iniquities of her priests, who shed righteous blood in the midst of her,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:14",
      "text": "NUN. her watchmen staggered in the streets, they were defiled with blood in their weakness, they touched their raiment with it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:15",
      "text": "SAMECH. Depart ye from the unclean ones: call ye them: depart, depart, touch them not: for they are on fire, yea, they stagger: say ye among the nations, They shall no more sojourn there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:16",
      "text": "AIN. The presence of the Lord was their portion; but he will not again look upon them: they regarded not the person of the priests, they pitied not the prophets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:17",
      "text": "PHE. While we yet lived our eyes failed, while we looked in vain for our help. TSADE. We looked to a nation that could not save.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:18",
      "text": "We have hunted for our little ones, that they should not walk in our streets. KOPH. Our time has drawn nigh, our days are fulfilled, our time is come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:19",
      "text": "Our pursuers were swifter than the eagles of the sky, they flew on the mountains, in the wilderness they laid wait for us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:20",
      "text": "RECHS. The breath of our nostrils, our anointed Lord, was taken in their destructive snares, of whom we said, In his shadow we shall live among the Gentiles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:21",
      "text": "CHSEN. Rejoice and be glad, O daughter of Idumea, that dwellest in the land: yet the cup of the Lord shall pass through to thee: thou shalt be drunken, and pour forth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:22",
      "text": "THAU. O daughter of Sion, thine iniquity has come to an end; he shall no more carry thee captive: he has visited thine iniquities, O daughter of Edom; he has discovered thy sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:25",
      "text": "TETH. The Lord is good to them that wait for him: the soul which shall seek him",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:26",
      "text": "is good, and shall wait for, and quietly expect salvation of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:27",
      "text": "TETH. It is good for a man when he bears a yoke in his youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:28",
      "text": "He will sit alone, and be silent, because he has borne it upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:30",
      "text": "JOD. He will give his cheek to him that smites him: he will be filled full with reproaches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:31",
      "text": "For the Lord will not reject for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:32",
      "text": "CHAPH. For he that has brought down will pity, and that according to the abundance of his mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:33",
      "text": "He has not answered in anger from his heart, though he has brought low the children of a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:34",
      "text": "LAMED. To bring down under his feet all the prisoners of the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:35",
      "text": "to turn aside the judgment of a man before the face of the Most High,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:36",
      "text": "to condemn a man unjustly in his judgment, the Lord has not given commandment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:37",
      "text": "Who has thus spoken, and it has come to pass? the Lord has not commanded it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.38",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:38",
      "text": "Out of the mouth of the Most High there shall not come forth evil and good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:39",
      "text": "MEM. Why should a living man complain, a man concerning his sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.40",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:40",
      "text": "NUN. Our way has been searched out and examined, and we will turn to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.41",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:41",
      "text": "Let us lift up our hearts with our hands to the lofty One in heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.42",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:42",
      "text": "We have sinned, we have transgressed; and thou hast not pardoned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.43",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:43",
      "text": "SAMECH. Thou hast visited us in wrath, and driven us away: thou hast slain, thou hast not pitied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.44",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:44",
      "text": "Thou hast veiled thyself with a cloud because of prayer, that I might be blind,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.45",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:45",
      "text": "and be cast off. AIN. Thou hast set us alone in the midst of the nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.46",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:46",
      "text": "All our enemies have opened their mouth against us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.47",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:47",
      "text": "Fear and wrath are come upon us, suspense and destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.48",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:48",
      "text": "Mine eye shall pour down torrents of water, for the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.49",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:49",
      "text": "PHE. Mine eye is drowned with tears, and I will not be silent, so that there shall be no rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.50",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:50",
      "text": "until the Lord look down, and behold from heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.51",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:51",
      "text": "Mine eye shall prey upon my soul, because of all the daughters of the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.52",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:52",
      "text": "TSADE. The fowlers chased me as a sparrow, all mine enemies destroyed my life in a pit without cause,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.53",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:53",
      "text": "and laid a stone upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.54",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:54",
      "text": "Water flowed over my head: I said, I am cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.55",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:55",
      "text": "KOPH. I called upon thy name, O Lord, out of the lowest dungeon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.56",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:56",
      "text": "Thou heardest my voice: close not thine ears to my supplication.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.57",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:57",
      "text": "Thou drewest nigh to my help: in the day wherein I called upon thee thou saidst to me, Fear not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.58",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:58",
      "text": "RECHS. O Lord, thou hast pleaded the causes of my soul; thou hast redeemed my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.59",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:59",
      "text": "Thou hast seen, O Lord, my troubles: thou hast judged my cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.60",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:60",
      "text": "Thou hast seen all their vengeance, thou hast looked on all their devices against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.61",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:61",
      "text": "CHSEN. Thou hast heard their reproach and all their devices against me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.62",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:62",
      "text": "the lips of them that rose up against me, and their plots against me all the day;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.63",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:63",
      "text": "their sitting down and their rising up: look thou upon their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.64",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:64",
      "text": "Thou wilt render them a recompence, O Lord, according to the works of their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.65",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:65",
      "text": "THAU. Thou wilt give them as a covering, the grief of my heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:lamentations.3.66",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 3:66",
      "text": "Thou wilt persecute them in anger, and wilt consume them from under the heaven, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
